    <summary>Open-Source PlayStation Remote Play</summary>
    <description>
`chiaki-ng` is an open source PlayStation remote play project serving as the next-generation of Chiaki with improvements and ongoing support now that the original Chiaki project is in maintenance mode only. 

### Information

  - [Search chiaki-ng Documentation](https://streetpea.github.io/chiaki-ng/?q=)
  - [Discord](https://discord.gg/ZFPvd2vD) / [GitHub](https://github.com/streetpea/chiaki-ng) / [Reddit](https://www.reddit.com/user/Street_Pea_6693/)

### Initial setup

  See https://streetpea.github.io/chiaki-ng/setup/configuration/

### Using a non-PlayStation controller

  See https://streetpea.github.io/chiaki-ng/setup/controlling/#using-a-non-playstation-controller-with-chiaki-ng
   
### Remote Connection (with or without port-forwarding)

  See https://streetpea.github.io/chiaki-ng/setup/remoteconnection/

### Commands

Options:
  -?, -h, --help             Displays help on commandline options.
  --help-all                 Displays help, including generic Qt options.
  --profile profile
  --exit-app-on-stream-exit  Exit the GUI application when the stream session
                             ends.
  --registkey registkey
  --morning morning
  --fullscreen               Start window in fullscreen mode [maintains aspect
                             ratio, adds black bars to fill unsused parts of
                             screen if applicable] (only for use with stream
                             command).
  --dualsense                Enable DualSense haptics and adaptive triggers
                             (PS5 and DualSense connected via USB only).
  --zoom                     Start window in fullscreen zoomed in to fit screen
                             [maintains aspect ratio, cutting off edges of image
                             to fill screen] (only for use with stream command)
  --stretch                  Start window in fullscreen stretched to fit screen
                             [distorts aspect ratio to fill screen] (only for
                             use with stream command).
  --passcode passcode        Automatically send your PlayStation login passcode
                             (only affects users with a login passcode set on
                             their PlayStation console).

Arguments:
  command                    stream, list
  nickname                   Needed for stream command to get credentials for
                             connecting. Use 'list' to get the nickname.
  host                       Address to connect to (when using the stream
                             command).

